Deferrals - Deferred income is any receipts before the closing key date that represent revenue for any period after this date.
A document that represents company owned goods stored at a third party facility.
The amount that represents what's been accrued, reversed, and settled for a claim.

In accrual-based VAT accounting, the liability for VAT arises at the time of shipment or delivery of the invoice, that is, as soon as you enter a customer or vendor invoice. You always post the full amount of VAT.
A process by which accruals are distributed based on the accrual profile and planning data.
A calendar showing the leave or other time off that has been accrued by an employee.
A regular adjustment of the outstanding balance.

Tool that can be used to calculate and post accruals automatically. The following application components are based on the functions of the Accrual Engine: Manual Accruals Provisions for Awards Lease Accounting Engine
saddtcomp: FI-AA-ALC - SAP Asset Lifecycle Accounting for Utilities

sglossary: The quota entitlement calculated for a specific period in automatic absence quota accrual.
An object controlling the calculation and posting ofdistributions to the correct periods and originators.
The classification of the objects calculating and posting distributions.
A way of distributing accruals, for example, in accordance with the expected sales curve or equally over a specified period of time.
A parameter assigned to sales order items that controls whether revenue is deferred automatically and whether the point of recognition has been reached.

An entity for which accruals can be calculated and posted. An accrual object contains the data that is required to accrue a business transaction. To determine periodic accrual amounts, for example, data such as the total amount, the lifetime (that is, the period between a start and end date), and the calculation algorithm is needed. An accrual object is created within an application component. Depending on the application component, an accrual object either corresponds to an existing object like a purchase order or the user can manually create an accrual object. Example In the Purchase Order Accruals application component, the accrual object is based on the purchase order. The accrual object contains accrual subobjects that correspond to the purchase order items.
Group of accrual objects that serve a similar accrual purpose. For example, accrual object category <ZH>RENT</> could group together accrual objects that are used to accrue rental expenses.

An element for monitoring the period-based accrual calculation between the expenses posted in Financial Accounting and the accrued costs debited in cost accounting. This enables users to distribute the expenses recorded in Financial Accounting as accrued costs over several periods.
The period for which an accrual run should be executed. Example: For a monthly accrual, the accrual period could be January 1 to January 31.
A process by which accruals are assigned to the relevant financial periods.
Calculation method that is applied in the key date valuation to calculate accruals and deferrals. Accrual procedures are part of the 'accrual/deferral' class of calculation procedures.
A model used for distributing accruals, for example, by month or by quarterly period.
The number of days or hours that are accrued to an employee's time account.
Percentage rate or amount per transaction to be accrued in Financial Accounting in anticipation of rebates that have to be paid.
The rate, in hours or days, by which a vacation account is gradually increased, for example, two days vacation every month. The accrual rate is configured in the time account rule.
A process by which an accrual posting run is reversed.

A rule that defines time account processing. The rule is set up in the Fine-Tune phase of Business Configuration, such as automatic accrual, entitlement, or period end processing. For example, you can define that for each month two days are accrued or that 30 days are entitled per year. For data migration, you enter the accrual rule to define how to handle remaining holidays at the end of a year: They can be transferred to the next year, paid out, or set to zero.
A rule that determines how much time is to be posted to a time account and when accrual occurs. Time account accrual typically increases the balance of a time account.

Simulated outgoing royalties settlement in the Billing Engine to determine the amount that is already due to be paid to a licensor on this key date. This run triggers accruals postings in the Accrual Engine.

Characteristic in the Accrual Engine that controls the calculation of amounts for accruals and deferrals, and their posting based on accounting considerations. The accrual type classifies the accrual items, for example as Costs Revenue Receivables
saddtcomp: FI-AF-SAI - SAP S/4HANA for Accounting Integration

sglossary: A set of conditions used to represent the differences between cost accounting and financial accounting.
Total value of accruals that have been made per business transaction.

A function performed at a certain key date that is used to determine the correct income for the accounting period. Receipts and expenditures are assigned to the relevant period to determine expenses and revenues. Flows are generated by the accrual/deferral function in the Treasury component, and are transferred to Financial Accounting.

Enables the correct income to be determined for the accounting period. Receipts and expenditures are assigned to the period in which they arose to determine the expenses and revenues. Flows are generated by the accrual/deferral, and are transferred to Financial Accounting.

Accrual is a process to create accrual orders for posting to an account management system in order to balance the general ledger at the end of the day. Accrual type (area) specifies a type of accrual used to group payment items.

A  process to create orders for posting to an account management system in order to balance the general ledger at the end of the day. Each accrual type is mapped to a possible technical status of payment items.
The actual recording of revenue when earned or expenses when incurred regardless of when cash is received or disbursed.

A process used for assigning revenue to the correct accounting period for revenue that has already been posted or revenue that is expected. RE differentiates between the following accrual/deferral processes: Accrual of rents paid in advance Deferral of rents paid in arrears Sales accrual/deferral for contracts in which rent is determined by the reported sales
Automatic adjustment of accruals using correction postings for changes made subsequently to the article or its price.

(ICM) A mass data process that informs target systems about outstanding remuneration and retention entitlements in Incentive and Commission Management. You can use Commission Accruals Notification to support the approval process and partial release of accrued commission amounts.

An amount of money that aggregates over time. An initial budget is planned for the fiscal year. Accrual runs are scheduled, for example, every month or every quarter. During the accrual run, the amount of budget accrued over that period is calculated. This is the accrued balance.
(ICM) Commission that has been calculated in Incentive and Commission Management (ICM), but not yet sent to the disbursement system(s).

The costs that are not categorized as a business expense (additional costs), or costs that are valuated differently or distributed across periods differently in cost accounting than in Financial Accounting (valuation differences).

Discount that is calculated after the invoice has been issued, for example, based on rebates, claim settlements or cash discounts. Typically, these are rebates which are represented as an accrual for future payout.
A daily dividend condition where you can either enter value factor types with variable dividends or choose a fixed amount.
An expense that is recognized in an accounting period but not yet invoiced in that period. Accrued expenses are held on accrual accounts until they are invoiced.
The amount of interest calculated from the start of the term up until the key date, that takes account of the posted interest, plus the prorated interest not yet posted.
Posted interest on arrears and the corresponding share of unposted interest on arrears for the analysis period from the term start until the key date.
Expenses paid in arrears and revenues received in arrears that are transferred to an income statement in a prior period by using the postings "Other Payables" and "Other Receivables".
An expense that a company or a business has incurred but has not yet paid.
scompdesc: Excise Tax Solution on SAP Cloud Platform, with S/4 integration

sglossary: Revenue recognized in an accounting period but not yet invoiced in that period. Accrued revenue is held on accrual accounts until it is invoiced.
A tax included in the cost of purchases and payable to the tax authorities at regular intervals of time. Accrued tax is usually posted to a separate G/L account.

A type of commodity contract that is mainly used for commodity purchase from vendors in an unplanned scenario. This is a type of spot contract in which the accumulation occurs over a period of time before the 'Readyto Price' indicator is set. An accumulate to own contract is created after receiving the first load from a vendor; then the quantities from further loads are accumulated or updated to that contract.
The total property, resources, or items of value relative to a specific date.
Sum of depreciation charges taken to date on a fixed asset.
This condition is available for investment funds. It summarizes the accrued dividend flows of a period in a single dividend flow.
The distance driven by an employee during an accumulation period.
Points collected by a member.
The insured sums of all insurance policies against a specific peril that could be affected by the same loss event are entered and added to the in-force business.

The number of months in which the system adds together the number of days' sick leave that an employee takes. When an employee is sick, the system checks whether an employee is entitled to take sick leave by comparing the amount of sick leave (expressed in terms of months) that an employee has taken in the accumulation period with the amount of sick leave (expressed in terms of months) to which an employee is entitled in that period.
The time period in which the reported mileage is accumulated.
The place at which wastes are received, sorted, and grouped into larger units for transport.
A time interval in which all individual messages, which have accumulated within a notification for a specific destination system, are grouped together into one notification message.
Classification metric. Percentage of correctly predicted records. The higher the better.

A metric of the error matrix (also called confustion matrix). It is the proportion of predicted positive targets that were actually positive targets and predicted negative targets that were actually negative targets divided by all predictions.  Calculation formula is:(True Positive + True Negative)/total.  The degree to which the result of a measurement, calculation, or specification conforms to the correct value or standard.
The extent to which data objects correctly represent the real-world values for which they were designed.

The degree to which a measurable element adheres to a standard or known value while being free from error. An element may be precise, precision being a measure of detail, but not accurate, accuracy being a measure of correctness.

Information about the accuracy level of a workload for a given time slot. For example, a warehouse order could be expected to have a high level of accuracy, while an expected workload would be less accurate.

A provider of electronic funds transfer services in the United States, handling automated payments such as direct debit and direct credit. Companies that use ACH send a DME file with information about the payments to be made. ACH then carries out the payments for them.

The emission of acidifying substances such as SO2, NOX, etc., which have diverse impacts on soils, water, ecosystems, biological organisms and material (for instance, buildings). Forest dieback and fish mortality in lakes are examples of such negative effects.

A file that contains information about employers, employees, and contractual schedules of the employee. The file is generated by a set of computer routines. The file is known in Portuguese as 'arquivo de controle de jornada para efeitos fiscais'.
To confirm that you have read, understood, and will adhere to a policy of your organization.
To confirm the receipt of a scheduling agreement release.
Alert given one of the following statuses in the <ls>Alert Monitor</>: Hidden Forwarded Acknowledged The Alert Monitor interprets this alert as processed but does not delete it.

The last page of a report or a package of several related reports that the recipient must return to the sender. The layout of an acknowledgement of receipt is defined using an acknowledgement of receipt template.
A message sent back to the sender to confirm whether an asynchronous message has been correctly processed or not.
saddtcomp: BC-MOB - SAP NetWeaver Mobile - Use subcomponents

sglossary: ACORD is a non-profit organization whose mission is to facilitate the development and use of standards for the insurance, reinsurance, and related financial services industries. ACORD stands for Association for Cooperative Operations Research and Development.

A generic business process that covers all activities related to the lifecycle of both tangible and intangible assets, such as their acquisition or production, onboarding, maintenance, offboarding, and decommissioning.
A company acquired by another company during a purchase and sale transaction.
A main business process in the BART Server system during which all CDRs are acquired from the same external source and stored in the BART database.

A transaction type used when equipment is entered in the company stock for the first time, for example after it has been bought, leased or rented. You can send equipment directly to a usage site without having to post it to the contractor's yard, warehouse or storage location first.
The process of identifying the requirement for a certain good or material item, ordering it, and paying for it.
The costs involved in obtaining an asset, whether it is purchased externally or produced internally.
(ICM) Remuneration for the first acquisition of a transaction (e.g. contract).

The upper limit for valuation of an asset in the balance sheet. For external acquisitions, acquisition costs include all expenses for the acquisition including incidental acquisition costs, minus reductions to the purchase price. Incidental costs include: Freight charges Forwarding costs Commissions Costs for building a foundation, and so on Reductions in purchase price can be: Rebates Cash discounts Bonuses Price reductions because of defects Subsidies granted by a third party, and so on For in-house acquisitions, production costs include: Direct and indirect costs, including materials handling overhead Direct labor costs, including payroll overhead Special production costs Fair administrative expense (can be included)
saddtcomp: FI-AF-SAI - SAP S/4HANA for Accounting Integration

sglossary: The historical costs of obtaining a fixed asset, whether it is purchased or created.

sterm: acquisition cost of current fiscal year
sglossary: The sum of acquisition and production costs during the current fiscal year.
(ICM) Insurance company costs incurred as a result of concluding an insurance contract (for example, initial commission, overriding commission and so on).
Object that stores data on the document level (basic level), before it is further processed through quality validation and data enrichment.
Date of the customer's acquisition. This date is used for the customer lifetime value calculation.
A report listing all the asset acquisitions for a specific period.
Specifies whether, in the case of a tag query, PCo is to obtain the value of the queried tag from the OPC server synchronously or asynchronously in the query process.
A period of time during which all the CDRs that come from an external source are acquired, processed, and stored by the BART Server system in its database.

An acquisition tax is due on the cross-border movement of goods and services within the European Union. Acquisition tax must be applied by the receiving party at the local rate (but can also be posted as input tax). Any company that is entitled to reclaim input tax does not ultimately pay acquisition tax. When the incoming invoice is posted, the tax amount is posted both as a payable and as a receivable on the tax account. Acquisition tax is calculated on the base amount of the invoice when it is issued (at the latest, on the 15th day of the month following the month when the goods or services were acquired (In Germany, at the end of this month.) The tax rates vary between Member States, but correspond to the standard domestic rates in each country.
The fiscal year in which the asset acquisition took place.
saddtcomp: CA-JVA - Joint Venture und Production Sharing Accounting

sglossary: An expression that was created artificially by joining the initial letter or letters of each of the successive parts or major parts of a compound term, and can be pronounced as a single word, for example, "ABAP" or "BAPI."
To agree, as business partner, to be used as a reference for the company.

sterm: Act on the Participation of the Federation in Appointments to Bodies
sglossary: Act that came into force on April 24, 2015, that aims at the equal representation of women and men in bodies, in so far as the Federation may designate members of such bodies (§1 BGremBG).

An internal program that helps employees explore career development opportunities. This program can work with but is separate from other development initiatives at SAP. Act to Grow focuses on helping employees take an active role in their own professional development.
A period of employment for an employee in the artist regime. Acting jobs affect the employee's calculation of payroll and Social Security charges.

A physical process that occurs within SAP Auto-ID Infrastructure at a specified date, time, and location.  Examples of actions include packing a specific pallet, or loading a specific truck, on a specific date.
A script file that executes business logic at a particular point in time within the business object’s lifecycle. Actions can be triggered from the user interface or from events or other actions.
Represents the 'Then' part of a rule. The steps to be taken when a rule is satisfied are collectively called actions.
A business scenario-specific task, often with a recurring character. Preconfigured for a business scenario, available for all instances of this scenario.
An entity assigned to an individual node of a business object. It is used to implement a service (operation or behavior) of the business object.
scompdesc: BOPF Business Object Framework for ABAP

sglossary: A modify operation that is assigned to the behavior of a business object Actions can be related to an instance of a business object (default) or are static.

An optional element of a business object (BO) node that describes an operation performed on that node. When you perform the action, you must specify: The name of the action; the BO node on which the action is to be performed; the key for the instances on which it is to be performed; any input parameters that the action requires. The action then returns the set of objects that have been created or changed by it. Actions are always implemented by a specific method in the action interface. Actions can and should be reused in more than one BO node (not necessarily in the same BO).

Collection of permissions used to enforce authorizations in SAP User Management Engine. Every application defines its own set of actions and specifies the permissions assigned to the actions either in an XML file or (more seldom) dynamically in the code.

A function or process that is scheduled for a business object and is started either directly or later, on the basis of particular conditions. Actions can be performed either manually by employees or automatically by the system. The following are possible actions: mail, telephone call, visit, quotation, credit memo.
scompdesc: Communication Services: Mail, Fax, SMS, Telephony

sglossary: An object in SAP Exchange Infrastructure that represents a function within an application component that is not subdivided further. Actions divide up the process flow of an integration scenario. Actions in different application components can exchange messages with each other within an integration scenario.
Actions allow users to execute automations, workflows, or notifications in SAP and non-SAP systems.
Element in SAP Signavio Process Governance for modeling a workflow.
A function to start a user interaction.
scompdesc: Integration of Support into all SAP products

sglossary: Function which is performed with an object, for example, with a batch. Example Creation of an issue in SAP Quality Issue Management with chosen batches as reference objects.
An interface building block that handles the execution of the interface logic in the SAP application system by calling standard functions, customer functions, or BAPIs.
Something that a chatbot executes at a specific point when executing a skill. Examples include sending a message to the user, calling a webhook, or going to another skill.
A predefined action for a situation type that can help solve a situation.
The part of an intent that describes which operation (such as Display or approvePurchaseOrders) is intended to be performed on a semantic object (such as Purchase Order or Product).

An object that connects to the application or service called by a process step. Actions link the process context to the application context. They are configurable and reusable. The resources and results of an action are defined by their input and output parameters. These parameters are assigned to the corresponding application parameters. Actions can call the following applications WebDynpro components iViews interactive forms
The task, predefined by SAP or custom defined by the user, to be executed by a flow. Example To get order item details based on order ID or get the product details based on product ID.
The interaction a customer has with the Loyalty plan. The Loyalty plan is based around offering incentives to customers to take action, and rewarding them for doing so.

A planned activity (follow-up action) or task that is designed for reacting to a situation. The action is created in the transaction document or depending on a rule (action profile) for the transaction. Actions can be determined both at the header level of the transaction for the whole transaction and also for individual items. Actions can be scheduled (type of action and start requirement) started (manually or automatically) monitored An action can be implemented by a person, group of people or a system in the background. Example 1: When you create a complaint, a credit memo item is created and ensures that the warehouse stock is sorted. Example 2: A month before a contract expires, the responsible sales employee receives an activity with the category 'telephone' in his inbox to remind him to ring the customer and find out whether they wish to renew their contract.
A task performed by the system that may not be visible to the end user.

A logical grouping of tasks that is performed in a particular sequence. A set of tasks together performs one particular action. Action is a configuration element of the Process Configuration activity performed in the Central Software Deployment Manager. Example The action of installing an application on a system. This action includes a set of tasks such as, copying the setup file to the target system, executing the setup on the target system, and then deleting the setup file from the target system.
A description of how to reach the targets that have been set for an environmental objective.

A work process that can be defined as either reactive or proactive. &EXAMPLE& Health & Safety: A step or activity that must be taken to prevent an unsafe condition or event, such as safety training or a preventive maintenance task.
An event that is triggered when a control is selected at runtime.
saddtcomp: BC-DWB-JAV - SAP NetWeaver Developer Studio - Read SAP Note 1179668

sglossary: A response to a company or partner's request. Requests are made via  statuses.

An element on the user interface represented by a pushbutton that users can choose to perform different tasks when processing open items and working with payment release lists. &EXAMPLE& Assign items Display item log Pay items

Object of the Business Rule Framework (BRF). You use actions to define rules in the BRF. A rule usually comprises an expression and an action. If the rule returns the value TRUE, the action is executed.

The activity you perform to process policies. On the user interface, you can select various actions in the "Action" menu or as pushbuttons in the Action toolbar. Examples: Change Option, Risk Assessment
A measure taken when a rule's conditions are met.  Example Send discount email
A self-contained business transaction.

Procedure in call control for a JIT call where a logistical (for example, create delivery) or a technical (for example, print pick list) function is executed for a components group. An action controls the JIT call at the supplier.

Business process, relating to the handling of vehicles. This can be, for example, create vehicle, change vehicle, create purchase order, create sales order. Actions can be classified as being primary or secondary, with primary and secondary actions being non-hierarchical terms of equal value. Whether actions are considered to be primary or secondary by a certain user depends on his individual business processes. Actions could e.g. be split as follows: purchasing actions versus sales actions, or logistics actions (actions concerning the vehicle as such) versus financial actions (actions referring to payments).

Term from JAVA programming to describe a function that can be used to assign a font or to cut and insert a text. All functions in IS-M/AMC UI are actions to which a shortcut can for example be assigned.
Smallest entity of the amendment framework that allows you to what kind of changes the tax officer can perform when amending a form.
scompdesc: Public Sector Contract Accounts Receivable and Payable

sglossary: The first dependency type that could be used to infer characteristic values. Made obsolete in subsequent releases by procedures and constraints. When you run a download for the Internet Pricing and Configurator, actions are converted to procedures.
To perform a business transaction. For example: Document creation in a particular system.

A series of infotypes that are added, changed, completely or partially deleted, or delimited for a reason, for example, hiring, change of cost center, and leaving. The term "action" in Employee Central Payroll corresponds to the term "event" in Employee Central.
A rule that defines how the system should react when the corresponding conditions of a business rule are met.
(MFG-MII) A processing step in a transaction that can enable the following: Data input and output Web input and output Transformations Calculations Communications Flow control
scompdesc: SAP Manufacturing Integration and Intelligence (SAP MII)

sglossary: A particular activity that needs to be undertaken by the project team in order to achieve work package and project objectives.

An action defines navigation and user interaction for the Agentry client. Actions are composed of a series of action steps of varying types. An action is defined to allow the user to interact with the application in some way.
(OPU-GW) Prepackaged business logic attached to an entity type.
A program or Web page, accessible by using its uniform resource locator (URL), that can be associated with an external content type so that  users can perform the action on items of that type.

An operation that can be executed for objects (in the HCM context objects could be org unit, position, and person) in the Personnel & Organization component. The following action types are available: editing of an infotype, starting a process, starting a report
Intended manipulation of a proposed target structure which is memorized and taken into account during the next synchronization.

Method of capturing and executing application logic in River. An action consists of a set of pre-defined steps that are executed in a particular sequence. Actions can create, modify, and delete data stored in collections and can execute searches on collections. In addition, actions can invoke other actions, including calls to linked applications.

Activity that the system executes immediately in <ls>Production Planning and Detailed Scheduling</> (PP/DS) if a planning-relevant event occurs for a product. A planning-relevant event is, for example, a change to the product master or the arrival of a new sales order. As possible actions, the system can create a planning file entry immediately, or execute a product heuristic.

A business operation within production planning or production control. An action can be executed either automatically by the system or manually by the user. With automated processing, the action is triggered by an event and is executed automatically by the system. &EXAMPLE& In the case of automobile production, when a vehicle reaches a certain action point on the production line, shop papers are printed automatically.

Option that is made available to the WCL transaction user by the system in order to send various event messages. The actions that the user can carry out are dependent on the configuration of his or her event message profile. The user wants to send a "Delay", for example. The user's event message profile is configured in such a way that in the event handler detail view, for example, he or she is offered the actions "All events", "Delay" and "Arrival at customer". The user enters the data for an action and sends the event message to the SAP Event Manager.
An area in the agent desktop, where agents can trigger additional actions.
A toolbar that often includes a "New" button and an actions icon that contains context-specific actions.
A element of the GUI that replaces the application title bar and provides dedicated real estate at the top of the screen.

A screen element that can be used to start specific functions for notifications defined in Customizing. This activity can be an action or a task in the notification and includes telephone notes or printing an interim report for a customer.
A component in the Interaction Center (IC) which enables the agent to access any SAP transaction, customer transaction, or HTML session from a user interface.
Tool located in the SAP C-ROOM navigation area used for quick alerting on events in a room. The action box consists of two tools: assistant members
The top section on the Executive Dashboard that shows you all the issues generated and provides you with information about how to resolve each issue.
A function used as an interface for transferring data to create or change documents in the background.
A coded representation of an instruction to the recipient of an XML message. For example, 01 is the action code for Create, 02 for Change, and so on.

A flag instructing a receiver which operation is to be applied to a business object node. In cross-component processes based on the process agent framework, the responsible outbound agent identifies action codes for all business object nodes relevant for the follow-on process at the receiver end. The action codes are written to the message and sent to the receiver. The receiver then maps the action codes to core services that make the change in question Action code 01, for example, means create a new business object node.
A set of characters displayed in the reports indicating what a production operator did with an SFC.
An activity type which indicates that an action was successfully executed.

Function that defines which actions can follow each other in the handling of vehicles and which vehicle status change is linked to this in each case. Example: A vehicle, that the importer has ordered at the OEM has the vehicle status "ordered". After the OEM has confirmed the purchase order (after carrying out the action "confirm purchase order") the status is automatically changed to "purchase order confirmed". Primary and secondary action controls are different depending on whether the control refers to primary or secondary actions. Primary action control usually respresents the procurement process (ordering of a vehicle at the manufacturer), secondary action control the sales process (sale of the vehicle to the dealer). However, a subdivision into a logistics process and a financial process is also possible.
The sequence of actions and the internal processing statuses for a given business process.

Observed information in a notification message sent from an RFID device to SAP Auto-ID Infrastructure. The information is related to an action that has already been performed. Action data represents the current state of an object.
A container that NetWeaver Voice uses to exchange data between the client and the data connector.

Attributes that describe an action independently of the processing type. For example, the action definition 'order confirmation' is initially independent of whether it is sent as a letter (print output) or as a fax.
scompdesc: Communication Services: Mail, Fax, SMS, Telephony

sglossary: The person who creates or edits an action.

A process within the Post Processing Framework that checks whether the conditions for scheduling an action have occurred. When saving an order, for example, the action determination checks whether all data has been entered completely. If so, the action "Send order confirmation" is scheduled.
scompdesc: Communication Services: Mail, Fax, SMS, Telephony

sglossary: An activity type which indicates that an appropriate action could be determined.
The time when the tokens connecting the individual Loyalty members to the Loyalty Action are sent out in a channel. The action can be completed from this point onwards.

File of the Internet Communication Manager or SAP Web Dispatcher that contains actions for the modification of HTTP requests. A line in the action file defines precisely one modification action. HTTP header field modifications, such as deleting, changing, and adding HTTP header fields, or URL modifications, such as URL rewrite, URL forwarding, and filtering of URLs. All modification actions can be linked with conditions. The sequence in the action file defines the sequence of execution too. When an HTTP request arrives, the modification actions defined in the action file are processed in succession. In the event of a successful URL filtering or URL redirect, rule processing stops. In parameter icm/HTTP/mod_<xx> the action file is specified.</>
Grid within action control where action sequences and status sequences are set.
Individuals or groups who must review and approve a document before it can route to additional individuals or groups for review.
saddtcomp: MFG-CDS - Complex Assembly Manufact. for Defense & Security

sglossary: Engineering Change Order (ECO) actions, along with the information as to how to determine the SFC numbers to which the actions will be applied and where (the routing and operation) they are to be applied.

The key for a group of functions available for maintaining the master record in HR and the organizational plan in Organizational Management. The grouping ensures that only one function can be selected from an action group.

Component within the APO system used for automatically or manually executing actions before or during production. With automated processing, the system executes actions automatically with all planned orders as soon as they reach a specified action point in the course of production (printing of shop papers, production tracking, backflushing etc.). With manual processing, the user executes actions manually with reference to individual planned orders during pre-production in a controlled form (ATP check for components must precede release of orders etc.).
Specific combination of one or more action handlers along with when and where you want the system to execute them.
A trigger governing of when and where the action handler is executed during manufacturing.

An activity performed on a serviceable material in repairs processing. Actions are represented in the repair order as sub-items of the repair request item. Actions include: Repair item for managing repairs Loaner item for sending temporary replacements to the customer Debit memo item for billing for services performed Scrap item for recording that a serviceable material is irreparable and must disposed of

An object other than telephony, e-mail, or chat objects that can be transferred to the interaction center (IC) for queuing or for routing to IC agents.  &Example& Business transactions, such as SAP CRM sales and service orders and SAP ERP sales orders Faxes and letters
A task for an employee, created by the employee or the manager of the employee, as a reminder of something that needs to be done.

A Computer-Aided Process Planning (CAPP), Order Maintenance, or non-CAPP document required or affected by the implementation of an engineering change. The document is assigned to a change record and must be completed before the change record can be completed and closed.
saddtcomp: MFG-CDS - Complex Assembly Manufact. for Defense & Security

sglossary: An activity determined during an xSOP meeting. It is grouped within the process step for that meeting.
A communication service used for transferring action items to interaction center agents.

The limit represented by the highest or lowest value in a quality control chart. If the actual values fall outside these limits, a correction in the process is required and/or the cause of the change in the process must be determined.
Displays the actions scheduled for a document as well as their start conditions.
The report that provides information about shop floor activities including the history of production operator actions.
A record of activities and interactions.
A rule according to which an action found is inserted in the action list of an application document.
scompdesc: Communication Services: Mail, Fax, SMS, Telephony

sglossary: The set of data that a system triggering action sends to the Collaboration Supervisor.

The determination of business-related dependencies between actions. The action network is assigned to a planned order. This ensures that the actions belonging to this planned order can only be carried out in a defined sequence. A preceding action can have several succeeding actions and vice versa. &EXAMPLE& A partial confirmation for a planned order is only possible if the final confirmation has not yet been made.
The object(s) associated with a specific SAP AII action. An example is the pallets (action object) that are used to load (action) the truck.
A window that contains contextual information relevant to the user's current activities and documents, as well as the application currently in use.
FBI software feature that enables the mapping of application UI structure fields to business object (BO) action UI structure fields.
scompdesc: Reusable Components of Business Suite Foundation

sglossary: Outcome of closing the gap between the baseline scenario and the target headcount by means of setting policies and using the pool to move role headcount.
Corrective measures taken by the auditee to remediate the issues found during internal auditing.

Policy and restructuring changes that explore different methods of closing the gap between the baseline scenario and the strategic scenario. The action plan scenario is based on the actual employees projected by all the different actions that can occur, such as changes in policy, one-time actions, and restructuring.
A Module within Workforce Planning that allows the capturing of information related to actions, goals and strategies to implement change in order to mitigate the Risk of employee shortfalls.
A position on a production line that is used as a reporting point for backflushing or as a point for triggering specific actions in the SAP APO.
saddtcomp: SCM-APO-PPS - Production Planning and Detailed Scheduling
scompdesc: FND Integrated Product and Process Engineering

sglossary: A valuation method for an FMEA. The action priority is used to prioritize the actions of an FMEA with the aim of reducing risk. The action priority can have the values high, medium, and low.
A service for finding and processing actions during output processing for billing.
A collection of business object attributes that can be used for the Post Processing Framework to determine and execute actions.
scompdesc: Communication Services: Mail, Fax, SMS, Telephony

sglossary: Summary of various actions that can be used in a transaction type, or billing type. All actions of an action profile have certain common attributes, for example from the business object or date profile. You define actions in the action profile.

Allows you to determine a specific action profile using specific conditions. Action profile determination is based on the condition technique, and can be used during sales order processing or billing. The action profiles are determined using variable fields, that is, configurable fields, such as:  In sales orders: Sold-to party Transaction type Sales area  In billing: Billing unit Payer

A program that is necessary to start the action menu, for example, to perform actions on fields in the WebClient UI. You can perform actions such as showing if a person is online or offline, sending e-mails and SMS, and sending instant messages.

The reason why an action is performed. For example, if an employee's salary has increased, this might be because of a promotion or a change of location. The salary increase is then the "action" and the promotion or change of location is the "action reason". The term "action reason" in Employee Central Payroll corresponds to the term "event reason" in Employee Central.
The reason why a personnel action is performed. The action reason can be used, for example, for reporting the reasons why employees leave the company.

Record containing all data necessary for notifications to the municipality. The action record is generated for the <ZK>water</> division and given to the municipality so that it can levy waste water fees.
A subphase of a phase in the maintenance process.
The routing used to execute the actions defined in the action group.

Controls how the system handles allocated stock if the release check fails. With the action rule you specify whether or not stock, which has been allocated to an order whose release check has failed, should remain reserved for that order.

A business rule that defines the actions required in different time phases (precondition, preaction, and post action) for create, save as, and delete operations. Action rules are applied to items, item revisions, and datasets.
A feature that allows users to quickly find specific tasks in the system by typing a keyword in the search box at the top of every page.

Individual steps within an action definition. They include the following types: Retrieve Records Perform Action Set Value Branch Loop Exit For Each Alert User Action Variable Record Variable Recordset Variable Additional Input
Actions that were taken to avoid the occurrence of a failure or problem or to better detect potential failures or problems.
In Customizing for Actions, a template for each action is first created that, depending on the application, can be later enhanced.
An area on a dashboard that highlights key information and metrics related to a user's daily activities.
saddtcomp: BNS-ARI-BINV - SAP Ariba Buying and Invoicing
BNS-ARI-SIPM - SAP Ariba Supplier Information and Performance
BNS-ARI-SLP - SAP Ariba Supplier Lifecycle and Performance
BNS-ARI-SSS - SAP Ariba Strategic Sourcing Suite

sglossary: A physical process that is recorded in SAP Auto-ID Infrastructure. Examples include packing, moving, loading, and commissioning.
Classification of the actions that can be used in Audit Management or FMEA to avoid or resolve problems. Action types can be, for example, corrective actions or preventive actions.
saddtcomp: QM-PT-FA - Failure Mode and Effects Analysis

sglossary: A type of action that can help solve a situation. Possible action types are 'navigation' (to another app) or 'callback'.
A classification of posting rules for data processing.

Activation parameter used to determine the rule strategy. The action type corresponds to the manipulation technique of the calling transaction. Possible manipulation techniques include creating, changing, and copying. These values are hard-coded in the SAP R/3 System and are transferred to SAP APO from the calling application. The values are assigned by the SAP R/3 sales order, the SAP CRM sales order, and backorder processing in SAP APO as follows: Create: A Change: B Copy: C In the case of stock transfers in SAP R/3, the value for the action type remains initial. You can use your own values for simulations on the SAP APO server.
Action validations check whether a specific action can be executed on a given node instance.
scompdesc: BOPF Business Object Framework for ABAP

sglossary: The duration when the recipient of the Loyalty action can fulfil its requirements to earn rewards. In the case of token-based Loyalty actions, this starts at the time when the personalization token is sent to the customer and not when it is clicked.

A specified threshold that requires action to be taken once it is reached. In risk assessment, if measured exposure to an agent exceeds the action value, organizations must take steps to treat the risk.
Used to store data inside of an action definition. There are two primary types of action variables: Record Variable Recordset Variable
An action that requires the user to make an entry in a dialog box. This action cannot be executed in the background.
Column inside a list or hierarchical list (tree) component containing one or more one-click action controls.
A view that displays a list of available actions in the process builder.

A checkpoint that is assigned to a checkpoint group using the addition ID of the statements ASSERT, BREAK-POINT or LOG-POINT. The behavior of an activatable checkpoint is controlled either by group-specific or program-specific activation settings. Program-specific settings apply to all activatable checkpoints in a program and overwrite the settings of the corresponding checkpoint group.
An action used to indicate that an RFQ request item, a request for quote item or a supplier quote item that was deactivated is once again relevant for the bidding process.

To perform a guided initial activation flow of a user account, which includes logging on via SAP Universal ID, linking user accounts to SAP Universal ID, and authorizing Built-In Support to act on behalf of this linked user account.
scompdesc: Integration of Support into all SAP products

sglossary: To make an optional line item in a contract available for sourcing or to make an optional line item in a purchase order available for ordering. Typically, in Customizing, you schedule the Options Handler Report to automatically activate options when their period of performance starts, provided that they have been exercised by a purchaser. Alternatively, you can activate options manually.
Allow the Customizing settings within a BC Set to overwrite those in the system.
The initial check and then moving of the current organizational structure from the planning area to the active area.
saddtcomp: LOD-FIN-FND - SAP FIN OD Foundation Topics

sglossary: A function in SAP software that activates a group of further functions that allows people with disabilities access to information technology and their applications. Examples of such functions include a braille display or a screen reader for blind users or users with low vision.
An app with which SAP S/4HANA Cloud customers selectively activate and adopt new features.

As soon as a medication order is activated, the user can process the corresponding events (e.g. administer the drug). The pharmacist who checked the ordered drug (the recipe) can activate the order, for example, as a control.

(CA-ATP) Agreed WebGUI self-service configuration app name for the activation of the product allocation functionality in advanced Available-to-Promise (aATP) in SAP S/4HANA Cloud. The activation is executed in the Configure Your Solution app. Note that in SAP S/4HANA, the product allocation functionality in aATP is activated in the SAP Customizing Implementation Guide (transaction SPRO > Cross-Application Components > Advanced Available-to-Promise (aATP) > Product Allocation (PAL) > Activate Product Allocation).
A configuration step that allows you to activate workflows for maintenance orders.
A process that makes an object available to the runtime environment Activation generates runtime objects, which are accessed by application programs and screen templates.
scompdesc: ABAP Workbench, Java IDE and Infrastructure

sglossary: The process of transferring a bean instance. For stateful session beans it is the transfer from secondary storage to memory. For entity beans it is the transferr from Passive to Ready (active) state. The opposite of passivation.
The transfer of master data from the staging area into primary persistence. This movement occurs following the approval of a change request.

The enablement of a resource in the SAP Master Data Services studio (by a data architect), that creates a runtime object in the SAP Master Data Services repository. Activated resources can then be used in real and simulated data consolidation processes.
An attribute of rules that sets the date and time when a version of the rule supersedes the previous one.

An operation performed by either the Compensation Specialist or the HR Administrator once the line manager has approved the suggested salary increases, bonuses or LTI grants in SAP Manager Self-Service. Upon activation, the compensation process status is set to 'Active' and the secondary infotypes are updated/generated accordingly.

Last step in the solution package based implementation process (using the implementation functions of the Solution Builder) - preceeded by scoping and personalization. The activation process writes the configuration content relevant for the implementation scope into the system tables (application and configuration tables), thus making the applications ready to use.
A process in the solution builder that makes a solution or a scenario active in a customer's SAP system.

A person who activates authorization profiles and authorizations to make them effective in the SAP System. An activation administrator can change only the profiles and authorizations specified in his or her own authorization profile and can also delete active versions of profiles and authorizations.
An group of activation and optimization services and related support offerings under the SAP Services and Support portfolio.

A contribution to be paid (as of January 1, 2018) by employers who allow their employees to be inactive for a full quarter. Employees can apply for this work exemption irrespective of their status (blue-collar/white-collar worker), their length of service, and their age. The employer’s contribution rate depends on the employee’s age at the start of the work exemption and is relevant for employers for whom the Collective Bargaining Agreement Act (CBA) of December 5, 1968 applies. The contribution is collected by the National Office for Social Security and is included in the DmfA.
Date from which document splitting is activated.
scompdesc: Data Migration for General Ledger Accounting

sglossary: The date on which a task which was created on an earlier date is set to  active and becomes visible to the user.
A string of numbers and letters which is used to activate an application service provider for an account.
Link between a table field and a Business Configuration Set, created during activation of the BC Set to protect the values in the table field from being overwritten accidentally.
A record generated when an ABAP Dictionary object is activated. The activation log contains all error messages, warnings and other information returned by the activation program.
A record automatically created when a BC Set is activated. It contains all warnings and other information returned by the activation program.

Property of a drug which describes whether it can be ordered at the curent time. &EXAMPLE& Inactive: New in the catalog, period of validity is missing Preactive: Can be ordered in future; Period of validity is defined Active: Can be ordered Deactivated: Can no longer be ordered
A person designated as responsible for activating solutions and scenarios in the solution builder.
A period of time after which the system sets the status of an entitlement to "Active". During summarization, the system only considers entitlements with status "Active".
Date on which the global employee becomes part of the host company and starts his or her new assignment.

sterm: activation service for collaboration of SAP Enterprise Product Development
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate the "collaboration" capability that is available within SAP Enterprise Product Development.

sterm: activation service for connected products of SAP Enterprise Product Development
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate the "connected products" capability that is available within SAP Enterprise Product Development.

sterm: activation service for experience management for SAP Commissions
sglossary: A service that helps customers identify areas for improvement in end-user experience in the activation of SAP Commissions.

sterm: activation service for innovation management of SAP Enterprise Product Development
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate the "innovation management" capability that is available within SAP Enterprise Product Development.

sterm: activation service for manufacturing with SAP S/4HANA Cloud, public edition
sglossary: A service that helps manufacturing customers activate SAP S/4HANA Cloud, public edition.

sterm: activation service for product innovation management of SAP Enterprise Product Development
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate the "product innovation management" capability that is available within SAP Enterprise Product Development.

sterm: activation service for SAP S/4HANA Cloud for projects, collaborative project management
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate the SAP S/4HANA Cloud for projects, collaborative project management capability.

sterm: activation service for SAP S/4HANA Cloud for projects, resource management
sglossary: A service that helps customers activate SAP S/4HANA Cloud for projects, resource management capability.
Set of objects to be processed by the mass activation program.
A status variable indicating whether an RFQ request item, a request for quote item or a supplier quote item is relevant for the bidding process.

Indicates whether an assortment module is active or inactive. An assortment module can be created so that it is inactive initially. At this point it is not yet ready to be assigned to plants. Only once it has been activated can it be managed actively in plants. The activation status of a module cannot be changed once it has been assigned to a plant.
An indicator that shows the status of an entry. It can be "active" or "inactive". If an entry is marked inactive, it doesn't appear in any dropdown list and cannot be used.
Indicates whether or not a particular demand influencing factor (DIF) occurrence is taken into account in the forecast calculation. Only active DIF occurrrences are taken into account.
An table attribute used to determine if a table can be activated directly from the ABAP Dictionary, or whether the table runtime object must first be generated with a C program.

The classification of a feeder system connection that determines how and at what time data are copied from the feeder system to the statutory reporting component. The possible activation types are online integration and integration for list output.

Repository object that contains activation settings for checkpoints that can be activated. An activation variant can contain settings for checkpoint groups and compilation units. The creation of activation variants and the maintenance of activation settings take place using the transaction SAAB.
Having a status that indicates that an RFQ request item, a request for quote item or a supplier quote item is relevant for the bidding process.

Status of an SAP Application Server, which is displayed in the server overview (transaction SM51). 'Active' is the "normal" status of an application server. It receives requests and processes them, or creates requests itself and sends them to other servers.

An editing status value of an R/3 online document. This value tells the SAP System that the document has been edited and can now be translated. When a document is activated, its contents are permanently linked to the current version number. When an active document is maintained, the system changes the editing status to "Raw version" and increments the version number.
A consent life cycle status of a consent indicating that the consent record is active an valid.
Status of an entry when the business process specialist/administrator has made it available to the users, e.g. actions, quick polls, agreements.
Object status indicating that the object (for example, auction or RFQ) can receive bids. The object automatically becomes active when the start date and time have been reached.
An alert status in Budget Monitoring.
A status you can assign to objects or infotype records in Personnel Management. The status "active" means that an object or infotype record is currently usable.
Indicating that an object is valid and can be used.

(1) Object status indicating that the contract attribute or condition can be used in a contract. A contract attribute or condition is set to active by the contract owner, contract administrator, or the attribute creator. (2) Object status indicating that the contract is valid. A contract is set to active by the contract owner (or other contract authors who have authorization), when the contract details are finalized. The contract  remains in active status until its status is changed manually or the end-date specified in the contract is reached at which point the contract may expire or be up for renewal.

A credit account with Orbian. It is used to post: Incoming Orbian Credits, which a company has received from its customers for payment Outgoing Orbian Credits, which a company has used to pay its vendors Any applicable fees and charges associated with an Orbian transaction Every Orbian Member has at least one active account per currency with Orbian.
A synthetic account or multidigit account for which only a debit balance is possible at the end of the day. An example of an active account is a loan account.
An account in the chart of accounts to which journal entries are posted. Accounts can be defined in the chart of accounts as either a title or an active account.

The analysis step that is displayed in the analysis step display. You can make selections in an active analysis step, if the representation type allows for it. In the analysis path display, the thumbnail of the active analysis step is highlighted.
Represents the current value of a CDS annotation. This value can be defined in the CDS view itself or is inherited from the underlying data sources or data elements.
An application that is currently running in the foreground.
The location used for the permanent storage of the active instances  of master data after changes have been approved by a change request process.
The read-only version of the organizational structure that is accessed by other application areas.  You cannot edit or update the organizational structure in the active area.
saddtcomp: LOD-FIN-FND - SAP FIN OD Foundation Topics

sglossary: Deliberate attempt to evade system security and alter the system.
A supplier bid in a sourcing event that has been accepted, and has not been rejected, traded, cancelled, or replaced, and that is not currently processing or expired.
Inspection of the available budget at release, change, or approval of a purchase order or a manual supplier invoice.
A method to enforce a tighter spending policy in the organization.
An Eligible Cloud Service that Customer has deployed and that has not been decommissioned.

The currently activated survivorship rule configuration. Not necessarily the one used to calculate the current best record, as that best record may have been calculated from a previous version that was different.
A configuration that is currently online.

A set of approved data describing an entity object, such as a medicinal product, pharmaceutical product or medical device. This information can be used to publish an agency record to regulatory agencies in the required format.
scompdesc: SAP for Identification of Medicinal Products

sglossary: A database that is replicated to a standby database in a warm standby  application.

A building’s start and end dates in the SAP Carbon Impact system, indicating when a building becomes active or goes offline from the building portfolio. For example, a building may be owned or occupied for a number of years and is used in a baseline inventory of energy and emissions, and subsequently is sold or the occupant moves out of that building.

A day when a product is available for sale in a specific location and the following conditions are fulfilled: The location is open. The product is listed. No ignore DIF is active. For example, active days can be used as input for week scaling.

A Windows-based directory service. The Active Directory stores information about objects on a network and makes this information available to users and network administrators. The Active Directory: enables network users to access permitted resources anywhere on the network using a single logon process provides network administrators with an intuitive, hierarchical view of the network and a single point of administration for all network objects
A Microsoft network service that maps the names of network resources to their respective network addresses, enabling users to locate resources and services distributed throughout the network.
The currently valid purchasing document that SRM uses for business processing; in contrast to an historical version or a change version.
All document splitting processes that you can set up in Customizing.
A person who is currently working in the company.
A component of apparent energy which is actually used to do work.
Ingredient of a drug which triggers an effect or contains the necessary agent.
saddtcomp: IS-PHA-REG - SAP for Identification of Medicinal Products

sglossary: An installation of SAP Business One Cloud which is identified by the installation number accessible from within such installation.

An object instance that incorporates the outcome of approved changes in a change request process and that is either ready for replication or that has already been replicated. Active instances reside in the active area.
